  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 3507d679efa283143b52308c9a6a3292, type: 3}
  m_Name: Question_3
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::QuestionData
  question: In which of the following eras of computing did an IBM system beat a
    chess champion, a robot drive itself down a 131-mile desert trail, and IBM Watson
    beat two Jeopardy! grand champions?
  answers:
  - Era of AI
  - Era of Programming
  - Era of Tabulation
  maxSelections: 1
  correctAnswerIndices: 00000000
  correctMessage: "All of those events occurred in the Era of AI. In 1997, IBM\u2019s
    Deep Blue beat the world\u2019s chess champion by processing over 200 million
    possible moves per second. In 2005, a Stanford University robot drove itself
    down a 131-mile desert trail. And in 2011, IBM\u2019s Watson defeated two grand
    champions in the game of Jeopardy!"
  incorrectMessage: Not quite. Consider which era of computing is happening now.
